Best dish of the night was their shrimp and corn tamale. Shrimp was cooked to perfection, and the sauce was just fantastic. My sixteen spice chicken was also delicious.  Mesa Grill was not kid friendly, but I should've known that. They don't really make adjustments to their dishes (less spicy, for example). Our waiter recommended the quesadilla for my 2 year old, but it was still too spicy for him. The adults had no problem devouring it though.  Had to take away one star because I did not care for their signature pork tenderloin at all.

